The paper focuses on detecting P2P botnets in IoT devices, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR) and networking (cs.NI). The use of a permissioned Byzantine Fault Tolerant (BFT) blockchain also suggests a potential fit for distributed computing (cs.DC) and distributed systems (cs.DS). Finally, the design of AutoBotCatcher involves the development of software components, which could fall under software engineering (cs.SE).
